                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Interesting viewpoint.  But in most programming contexts what we need is data structures.  Taking the linked article&apos;s &quot;Dog&quot; example.  Yes, you can&apos;t change a real-world dog&apos;s weight by setting an attribute ... but a &lt;code&gt;new Dog()&lt;/code&gt; is not a dog.  It is object that holds information about a dog.  And for that usage, it is natural to be able to correct an incorrectly recorded weight.&lt;/span&gt;

