                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Real world or not, yegor is completely right.  If what you have is truly a &quot;Struct&quot; and you don&apos;t need to write any code that references it by name, put it in a hashtable or other data structure.  If you do need to write code for it then put it as a member of a class and put the code that manipulates that variable in the same class and omit the setter &amp;amp; getter.  PS. although I mostly share yegor&apos;s viewpoint, I have come to believe that annotated beans without code are somewhat useful data structures--also getters are sometimes necessary, setters shouldn&apos;t ever exist.&lt;/span&gt;

